ciscoWirelessPhyMIB.name: ciscoWirelessPhyMIB

revisions.description: Fixed minor typo in spelling of Duplexer Changed valid range for p2mpSuMeasuredPower
Redefined p2mpDenyService Redefined p2mpLoopbackTable Added a second index for p2mpSuPowerScanTable

ciscoWirelessPhyMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 W Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: wireless-nms@cisco.com
ciscoWirelessPhyMIB.description: This is the MIB Module for the Cisco Wireless Radio Point to MultiPoint interface.

p2mpRadioPhyTable.name: p2mpRadioPhyTable
p2mpRadioPhyTable.description: This table provides facilities to configure the physical layer characteristics of the radio link. The objects in this table are supported on the head end and at the subscriber unit.

p2mpRadioPhyEntry.name: p2mpRadioPhyEntry
p2mpRadioPhyEntry.description: The entry of this table is created when the managed system detects a propDocsWirelessMaclayer interface. The entry is removed when the associated propDocsWirelessMaclayer interface is deleted from the ifTable.

p2mpSelfTest.name: p2mpSelfTest
p2mpSelfTest.description: This object is used to enable/disable self test. When set to true(1), the software tests the memory and hardware integrity shortly after the router powers up.

p2mpDiversityAntennaPresent.name: p2mpDiversityAntennaPresent
p2mpDiversityAntennaPresent.description: When true(1), this object indicates that a diversity antenna is being used to receive the wireless transmissions. When false(2), the radio system is using a single antenna to transmit and receive.

p2mpCableLoss.name: p2mpCableLoss
p2mpCableLoss.description: This object indicates the measured signal power loss in dB due to the cable connecting the radio to the main antenna. The hardware compensates for this cable loss by adjusting the receive and transmit gain appropriately. A value of 0 indicates no degradation in the signal due to the cable. The radio hardware can compensate for a cable loss of no more than 15 db. This cable loss applies to the main antenna only.

p2mpCableLossDiversity.name: p2mpCableLossDiversity
p2mpCableLossDiversity.description: This object indicates the measured signal power loss in dB due to the cable connecting the radio to the diversity antenna. The hardware compensates for this loss by adjusting the receive and transmit gain appropriately. A value of 0 indicates no degradation in the signal due to the cable. The radio hardware can compensate for a cable loss of no more than 15 dB. This cable loss applies to the diversity antenna only.

p2mpDenyService.name: p2mpDenyService
p2mpDenyService.description: Indicates if the service is disabled in the unit. For Head-end unit, if this object has the value of 'true', the link is in loopback mode; otherwise the link is enabled for transmitting / receiving data. For Subscriber unit, if this object has the value of 'true', the subscriber unit service is disabled; otherwise, the subscriber unit is enabled for transmitting / receiving data

p2mpClockRefExt.name: p2mpClockRefExt
p2mpClockRefExt.description: This object controls the use of external reference clock for IF module as follows: 'true(1)' - an external reference clock is used 'false(2)' - an internal reference clock is used.

p2mpCommonTrapEnable.name: p2mpCommonTrapEnable
p2mpCommonTrapEnable.description: When set to true(1), the notifications common to the head end and subscriber unit are enabled. When set to false(2), these notifications are disabled. The notification controlled by this object are: - p2mpRadioPhyFailNotification - p2mpTrapRfSupplyVoltage - p2mpTrapRfRxOsc - p2mpTrapRfTxOsc - p2mpTrapRfTemp - p2mpTrapRfCommLinkError - p2mpTrapTxPower - p2mpTrapRfStatusChange

p2mpLastPhyFailureType.name: p2mpLastPhyFailureType
p2mpLastPhyFailureType.description: This object indicates the last physical link failure that resulted in a p2mpRadioPhyFailNotification trap. none(1) - no failure p2mpHwConfigUnsupported(2) - The radio subsystem has detected that the configuration requested is not supported by the hardware. The p2mpLastPhyFailureReason variable will indicate which configuration parameter is not supported. p2mpHwConfigMismatch(3) - The radio subsystem has detected that the combination of the configuration parameters requested is inconsistent and cannot be supported. The p2mpLastPhyFailReason variable will indicate the configuration parameter that causes the mismatch. p2mpHwInitFailure(4) - The radio subsystem has failed to initialize the hardware. This implies that there is a critical error condition in the associated hardware. The p2mpLastPhyFailReason specifies the reason why the init failed. p2mpHostIfCommLinkError(5) - The host could not communicate with the IF module. p2mpAutoCableCompFailure(6) - Failed to achieve automatic cable compensation due to loss of Tx signal.

p2mpLastPhyFailureReason.name: p2mpLastPhyFailureReason
p2mpLastPhyFailureReason.description: This is a text string that describes the last physical link failure identified by p2mpLastPhyFailureType.

p2mpRfTable.name: p2mpRfTable
p2mpRfTable.description: This table contains information about the state of the radio frequency resources used by the radio system. Physically each RF resource may be realized by one antenna and its associated control hardware. A single antenna and its associated electronics may act as more than 1 RF resource. When an RF resource acts as both a transmit and receive resource, the transmit and receive frequency ranges may overlap.

p2mpRfEntry.name: p2mpRfEntry
p2mpRfEntry.description: This represents one entry in the p2mpRfTable. An entry is created in this table when the managed system detects a RF resource. The entry is removed when the RF resource is removed from the wireless system.

p2mpRfIndex.name: p2mpRfIndex
p2mpRfIndex.description: This object, along with the ifIndex of the MAC layer, represents the index of this entry in the p2mpRfTable. Each entry in the table provides details on the state of the RF resources available in the system.

p2mpRfType.name: p2mpRfType
p2mpRfType.description: This object identifies the RF resource.

p2mpRfOpMode.name: p2mpRfOpMode
p2mpRfOpMode.description: This object specifies whether this RF resource can either transmit, receive, or do both.

p2mpTxFreqRangeMin.name: p2mpTxFreqRangeMin
p2mpTxFreqRangeMin.description: This object represents the minimum frequency at which this RF resource can transmit.

p2mpTxFreqRangeMax.name: p2mpTxFreqRangeMax
p2mpTxFreqRangeMax.description: This object represents the maximum frequency at which this RF resource can transmit.

p2mpRxFreqRangeMin.name: p2mpRxFreqRangeMin
p2mpRxFreqRangeMin.description: This object represents the lowest transmission frequency this RF resource can receive.

p2mpRxFreqRangeMax.name: p2mpRxFreqRangeMax
p2mpRxFreqRangeMax.description: This object represents the highest transmission frequency that this RF resource can receive.

p2mpMinTxPower.name: p2mpMinTxPower
p2mpMinTxPower.description: This object represents the minimum power that the RF subsystem can supply the antenna.

p2mpMaxTxPower.name: p2mpMaxTxPower
p2mpMaxTxPower.description: This object represents the maximum power that the RF subsystem can supply the antenna.

p2mpRfTemperature.name: p2mpRfTemperature
p2mpRfTemperature.description: This object represents the current temperature of the RF unit

p2mpRfTxOscState.name: p2mpRfTxOscState
p2mpRfTxOscState.description: This object represents the state of the transmit oscillator. The oscillator must be in oscillatorOk(1) state for the system to function properly.

p2mpRfRxOscState.name: p2mpRfRxOscState
p2mpRfRxOscState.description: This object represents the state of the receive oscillator. The oscillator must be in oscillatorOk(1) state for the system to function properly.

p2mpRfSupplyVoltageState.name: p2mpRfSupplyVoltageState
p2mpRfSupplyVoltageState.description: This object specifies whether the voltage supply to the RF unit is within specifications or not. Voltage specifications are hardware dependent.

p2mpRfStatus.name: p2mpRfStatus
p2mpRfStatus.description: This object specifies whether the RF resource is functioning properly. If it is functioning properly then it will be online(1), else offline(2). At the Subscriber Unit, this object will reflect offline(2) if p2mpTxMuteEnable in the p2mpSuRadioPhyTable is true(1).

p2mpRfLoopbackSupported.name: p2mpRfLoopbackSupported
p2mpRfLoopbackSupported.description: This object indicates if the RF unit supports loopback. When true(1), the user can configure loopback using the objects in p2mpLoopbackTable. When false(2), any attempt to configure RF loopback will fail.

p2mpDuplexerTable.name: p2mpDuplexerTable
p2mpDuplexerTable.description: This table contains information about the Duplexers available for use on the system. A Duplexer is a mechanical device, that acts as a band pass filter when installed in an RF resource. Normally a RF resource is capable of operating over a wide frequency range. To operate at restricted frequencies, the user has to own that part of the frequency spectrum. Since the user may not own parts of the frequency spectrum over which the RF resource may operate, a duplexer is installed at the RF. This restricts the RF resource to operate in the passband defined by the duplexer.

p2mpDuplexerEntry.name: p2mpDuplexerEntry
p2mpDuplexerEntry.description: This represents one entry in the p2mpDuplexerTable. Each entry contains information about the duplexers capabilities and the associated RF resource. An entry is created in this table when the managed system detects a RF resource. The entry is removed when the RF resource is removed from the wireless system.

p2mpDuplexerIndex.name: p2mpDuplexerIndex
p2mpDuplexerIndex.description: This object, along with ifIndex, uniquely identifies an entry in this table. Each entry contains information about the duplexer's capabilities and also identifies the associated RF resource.

p2mpDuplexerRF.name: p2mpDuplexerRF
p2mpDuplexerRF.description: This object identifies the RF resource associated with this duplexer.

p2mpDuplexerLoPassbandMinFreq.name: p2mpDuplexerLoPassbandMinFreq
p2mpDuplexerLoPassbandMinFreq.description: This object identifies the minimum frequency in the low passband that this duplexer will pass through without attenuation.

p2mpDuplexerLoPassbandMaxFreq.name: p2mpDuplexerLoPassbandMaxFreq
p2mpDuplexerLoPassbandMaxFreq.description: This object identifies the maximum frequency in the low passband that this duplexer will pass through without attenuation.

p2mpDuplexerHiPassbandMinFreq.name: p2mpDuplexerHiPassbandMinFreq
p2mpDuplexerHiPassbandMinFreq.description: This object identifies the minimum frequency in the high passband that this duplexer will pass through without attenuation.

p2mpDuplexerHiPassbandMaxFreq.name: p2mpDuplexerHiPassbandMaxFreq
p2mpDuplexerHiPassbandMaxFreq.description: This object identifies the maximum frequency in the high passband that this duplexer will pass through without attenuation.

p2mpDuplexerReceivePassband.name: p2mpDuplexerReceivePassband
p2mpDuplexerReceivePassband.description: This object indicates which of the two passbands are being used to receive transmissions. The RF Resource can receive on either of the duplexer passbands. loPassband(1) - The RF Resource is receiving on a frequency in the low passband. hiPassband(2) - The RF Resource is receiving on a frequency in the high passband.

p2mpDuplexerTxInsertionLoss.name: p2mpDuplexerTxInsertionLoss
p2mpDuplexerTxInsertionLoss.description: This object represents the loss in 'dB' that would result in the transmission path due to the duplexer.

p2mpDuplexerBurnDate.name: p2mpDuplexerBurnDate
p2mpDuplexerBurnDate.description: This object indicates the date when the revision information was programmed into non-volatile memory.

p2mpAntennaTable.name: p2mpAntennaTable
p2mpAntennaTable.description: This table contains information about the antennas available in the system.

p2mpAntennaEntry.name: p2mpAntennaEntry
p2mpAntennaEntry.description: An entry is created in this table when the managed system detects a RF resource. The entry is removed when the RF resource is removed from the wireless system.

p2mpAntennaIndex.name: p2mpAntennaIndex
p2mpAntennaIndex.description: This object, along with ifIndex, represents the index of this entry in the p2mpAntennaTable.

p2mpRfResource.name: p2mpRfResource
p2mpRfResource.description: This object identifies if the antenna is connected to the main or the diversity RF resource.

p2mpAntennaXDim.name: p2mpAntennaXDim
p2mpAntennaXDim.description: This object represents the dimension of the antenna in the X direction.

p2mpAntennaYDim.name: p2mpAntennaYDim
p2mpAntennaYDim.description: This object represents the dimension of the antenna in the Y direction.

p2mpAntennaType.name: p2mpAntennaType
p2mpAntennaType.description: This object represents the antenna type. For example, 'dish-antenna'.

p2mpAntennaDescr.name: p2mpAntennaDescr
p2mpAntennaDescr.description: This object is used to describe the antenna. For example, it could be used to identify the manufacturer like in 'Manufactured by Watkins Johnson'.

p2mpAntennaGain.name: p2mpAntennaGain
p2mpAntennaGain.description: This object represents the receive and transmit gain of this antenna.

p2mpAntennaPolarization.name: p2mpAntennaPolarization
p2mpAntennaPolarization.description: This object represents the polarization of the antanna.

p2mpLoopbackTable.name: p2mpLoopbackTable
p2mpLoopbackTable.description: This table provides facilities to establish loopback points to exercise various sections of the hardware.

p2mpLoopbackEntry.name: p2mpLoopbackEntry
p2mpLoopbackEntry.description: This represents one entry in the p2mpLoopbackTable. It is created when the managed system detects a propDocsWirelessMaclayer interface. The entry is removed when the associated propDocsWirelessMaclayer interface is deleted from the ifTable.

p2mpLocalLoopbackMode.name: p2mpLocalLoopbackMode
p2mpLocalLoopbackMode.description: This object is used to configure the system in loopback mode prior to executing some system diagnostic tests. The user selects the point in the system where the data signal should be looped back. The diagnostic tests outlined in the user manual have to be manually executed to determine success or failure. Once all the tests are completed, normal operation is restored by setting this object to noLoopback(1). noLoopback(1) - no loopback fir(2) - loopback at the Finite Impulse Response (FIR) module. if(3) - loopback at the IF module. This exercises the FIR, and IF modules. rf(4) - loopback at the RF unit. This exercises the FIR, IF, and RF modules. This mode is supported only when p2mpRfLoopbackSupported is true(1).

p2mpLocalLoopbackAntenna.name: p2mpLocalLoopbackAntenna
p2mpLocalLoopbackAntenna.description: This object identifies the RF resource used for loopback testing. This object is not applicable for loopback testing when p2mpLocalLoopbackMode has a value of 'noLoopback(1)'.

p2mpLocalLoopbackChannel.name: p2mpLocalLoopbackChannel
p2mpLocalLoopbackChannel.description: This object identifies the channel being used to loopback the data. This object is not applicable for loopback testing when p2mpLocalLoopbackMode has a value of 'noLoopback(1)'.

p2mpLedTable.name: p2mpLedTable
p2mpLedTable.description: Entity (Light emitting diode) LED information. For each LED on the entity, an entry will exist in this table, describing the location and current status of that LED.

p2mpLedEntry.name: p2mpLedEntry
p2mpLedEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing the LED information. The entPhysicalIndex identifies the entity on which the LED's are present.

p2mpLedIndex.name: p2mpLedIndex
p2mpLedIndex.description: For a given entPhysicalIndex, this index value uniquely identifies an entry in the p2mpLedTable.

p2mpLedType.name: p2mpLedType
p2mpLedType.description: Indicates the type or label of the LED.

p2mpLedState.name: p2mpLedState
p2mpLedState.description: Indicates the state of the LED.

p2mpSuRadioPhyTable.name: p2mpSuRadioPhyTable
p2mpSuRadioPhyTable.description: This table contains information about the currently configured physical layer interfaces in the subscriber unit.

p2mpSuRadioPhyEntry.name: p2mpSuRadioPhyEntry
p2mpSuRadioPhyEntry.description: An entry containing the radio configuration information of the propDocsWirelessMaclayer interface in the subscriber unit. The entry is created when a propDocsWirelessMaclayer interface is detected in the subscriber unit. The entry is deleted when the associated propDocsWirelessMaclayer interface is removed.

p2mpSuTxMuteEnable.name: p2mpSuTxMuteEnable
p2mpSuTxMuteEnable.description: When true(1), this object indicates the subscriber unit transmission has been turned off for a duration indicated by p2mpSuTxMuteDuration. When false(2), this object indicates that the subscriber unit is transmitting.

p2mpSuTxMuteDuration.name: p2mpSuTxMuteDuration
p2mpSuTxMuteDuration.description: This object indicates the duration of time (in minutes) for which the subscriber transmission will be turned off.

p2mpSuPowerScanTable.name: p2mpSuPowerScanTable
p2mpSuPowerScanTable.description: This table contains information about the receive power measured at the different possible center frequencies.

p2mpSuPowerScanEntry.name: p2mpSuPowerScanEntry
p2mpSuPowerScanEntry.description: An entry containing the power related status information of the propDocsWirelessMaclayer interface in the subscriber unit. The entry is created when a propDocsWirelessMaclayer interface is detected in the subscriber unit. The entry is deleted after the associated propDocsWirelessMaylayer interface is removed.

p2mpSuPowerScanIndex.name: p2mpSuPowerScanIndex
p2mpSuPowerScanIndex.description: For a given ifIndex, this index value uniquely identifies an entry in the p2mpSuPowerScanTable.

p2mpSuCenterFrequency.name: p2mpSuCenterFrequency
p2mpSuCenterFrequency.description: This object indicates the frequency at which the receive power at the subscriber unit was measured.

p2mpSuMeasuredPower.name: p2mpSuMeasuredPower
p2mpSuMeasuredPower.description: This object represents the power measured at the frequency indicated by p2mpSuCenterFrequency.

p2mpHeAlcTable.name: p2mpHeAlcTable
p2mpHeAlcTable.description: This table contains Automatic Line Control (ALC) configuration information. It is supported at the head end only.

p2mpHeAlcEntry.name: p2mpHeAlcEntry
p2mpHeAlcEntry.description: An entry containing the ALC configuration information the propDocsWirelessMaylayer interface at the head end. The entry is created when a propDocsWirelessMaclayer interface is detected in the head end unit. The entry is deleted after the associated propDocsWirelessMaclayer interface is removed.

p2mpHeAlcEnable.name: p2mpHeAlcEnable
p2mpHeAlcEnable.description: This object is used to enable/disable ALC at the Head End. A value of true(1), indicates that ALC is enabled.

p2mpHeAlcInterval.name: p2mpHeAlcInterval
p2mpHeAlcInterval.description: This object represents the scheduling interval. It is the regular interval at which the ALC grant in Map is transmitted to the SU's

p2mpHeAlcNumMiniSlots.name: p2mpHeAlcNumMiniSlots
p2mpHeAlcNumMiniSlots.description: This indicates the number of minislots within each grant.

p2mpHeIntFreqTable.name: p2mpHeIntFreqTable
p2mpHeIntFreqTable.description: This table contains information about the state of the intermediate frequency subsystem in the radio system. This table is supported at the head end only.

p2mpHeIntFreqEntry.name: p2mpHeIntFreqEntry
p2mpHeIntFreqEntry.description: The entry of this table is created when the managed system detects a propDocsWirelessMaclayer interface in the head end unit. The entry is deleted when the associated propDocsWirelessMaclayer interface is removed.

p2mpHeIfTxOscState.name: p2mpHeIfTxOscState
p2mpHeIfTxOscState.description: This object indicates the state of the IF transmit oscillator. The oscillator must be in oscillatorOk(1) state for the system to function properly.

p2mpHeIfRxOscState.name: p2mpHeIfRxOscState
p2mpHeIfRxOscState.description: This object indicates the state of the IF receive oscillator. The oscillator must be in oscillatorOk(1) state for the system to function properly.

p2mpHeIfRefOscState.name: p2mpHeIfRefOscState
p2mpHeIfRefOscState.description: This object indicates the state of the IF reference oscillator. The oscillator must be in oscillatorOk(1) state for the system to function properly.

p2mpHeIfInpFreq.name: p2mpHeIfInpFreq
p2mpHeIfInpFreq.description: This object represents the IF input frequency.

p2mpHeIfOutFreq.name: p2mpHeIfOutFreq
p2mpHeIfOutFreq.description: This object represents the IF output frequency.

p2mpHeTrapEnable.name: p2mpHeTrapEnable
p2mpHeTrapEnable.description: When set to true(1), this enables the notifications that are specific to the head end. When set to false(2), these notifications are disabled.

p2mpRadioPhyFailNotification.name: p2mpRadioPhyFailNotification
p2mpRadioPhyFailNotification.description: A p2mpRadioPhyFailNotification is sent if the value of p2mpLastPhyFailureType changes due to the new failure being detected in the Radio interface.

p2mpTrapRfSupplyVoltage.name: p2mpTrapRfSupplyVoltage
p2mpTrapRfSupplyVoltage.description: The supply voltage to the RF resource has changed. The p2mpRfSupplyVoltageState specifies whether the supply voltage is in spec or not.

p2mpTrapRfRxOsc.name: p2mpTrapRfRxOsc
p2mpTrapRfRxOsc.description: The RF receive frequency oscillator has changed state. The p2mpRfRxOscState specifies the current state of the oscillator.

p2mpTrapRfTxOsc.name: p2mpTrapRfTxOsc
p2mpTrapRfTxOsc.description: The RF transmit frequency oscillator has changed state. The p2mpRfRxOscState specifies the state of the oscillator.

p2mpTrapRfTemp.name: p2mpTrapRfTemp
p2mpTrapRfTemp.description: The temperature of the RF module identified by p2mpRfIndex has exceeded a defined reference.

p2mpTrapRfCommLinkError.name: p2mpTrapRfCommLinkError
p2mpTrapRfCommLinkError.description: This trap indicates that the host and the IF module cannot communicate with the RF resource identified by p2mpRfType.

p2mpTrapTxPower.name: p2mpTrapTxPower
p2mpTrapTxPower.description: This trap indicates that the transmit power for the RF resource identified by p2mpRfType exceeded a predefined threshold.

p2mpTrapRfStatusChange.name: p2mpTrapRfStatusChange
p2mpTrapRfStatusChange.description: This trap indicates that the RF resource either came online(1) or went offline(2).

p2mpTrapHeIfRxOsc.name: p2mpTrapHeIfRxOsc
p2mpTrapHeIfRxOsc.description: The IF receive frequency oscillator has changed state.

p2mpTrapHeIfTxOsc.name: p2mpTrapHeIfTxOsc
p2mpTrapHeIfTxOsc.description: The IF transmit frequency oscillator has changed state.

p2mpTrapHeIfExtRefOsc.name: p2mpTrapHeIfExtRefOsc
p2mpTrapHeIfExtRefOsc.description: The IF Reference Frequency oscillator has changed state.

p2mpRadioPhyCompliance.name: p2mpRadioPhyCompliance
p2mpRadioPhyCompliance.description: The compliance statement for devices that implement Point to Multipoint wireless interfaces compliant with the Cisco Systems Inc. specification.

p2mpCommonRadioGroup.name: p2mpCommonRadioGroup
p2mpCommonRadioGroup.description: Mandatory group of objects implemented to configure a point to multipoint wireless radio.

p2mpCommonRfGroup.name: p2mpCommonRfGroup
p2mpCommonRfGroup.description: Mandatory group of objects implemented to tune the phy quality in a point to multipoint wireless radio.

p2mpCommonTestGroup.name: p2mpCommonTestGroup
p2mpCommonTestGroup.description: Mandatory group of objects implemented in the point to multi point wireless system for Testing the link.

p2mpRadioSuGroup.name: p2mpRadioSuGroup
p2mpRadioSuGroup.description: Group of objects implemented at the Subscriber unit.

p2mpRadioHeGroup.name: p2mpRadioHeGroup
p2mpRadioHeGroup.description: Group of objects implemented at the Head End.

p2mpRadioAntennaGroup.name: p2mpRadioAntennaGroup
p2mpRadioAntennaGroup.description: Group of objects implemented in the point to multi point wireless system for managing the antennas available in the system.
